title: 1812-C
statement: C. Digitstime limit per test1 secondmemory limit per test256 megabytesinputstandard inputoutputstandard outputInputThe first line contains a single integer $$$t$$$ ($$$1 \\le t \\le 32$$$) — the number of test cases.Each test case contains $$$n$$$ lines. The $$$i$$$-th line contains an integer $$$a_i$$$ ($$$1 \\le a_i \\le 9$$$).The sum of $$$n$$$ over all test cases doesn't exceed $$$155$$$.OutputFor each test case, print one integer — the answer.ExampleInput3 2 1 4 7 1 2 3 5Output8 7 30

processed.result:
You are given multiple test cases. Each test case consists of a sequence of integers.  For each test case, find the sum of all the integers in the sequence.

Input:

* The first line contains the number of test cases, $t$ ($1 \le t \le 32$).
* Each test case has a number of lines, $n$, where each line contains an integer $a_i$ ($1 \le a_i \le 9$). The total sum of $n$ across all test cases does not exceed 155.

Output:

* For each test case, print the sum of all the integers in the sequence.
You are given multiple sets of numbers. For each set, find the sum of the numbers.
